'''Protected areas of [[Hungary]]''' includes 10 [[national park]]s, 35 [[Landscape park (protected area)|landscape protection area]]s and 145 minor nature reserves. The national policy for governing and management of the protected areas is implemented by the [[Minister of Agriculture (Hungary)|Minister of Agriculture]] (State Secretary for the Environment). The first national park in Hungary at the [[Great Hungarian Plain]] is [[Hortobágy National Park]], established in 1973.
Types of protected areas: *National Park ({{lang-hu|Nemzeti park}}; abbr. NP) *Protected Landscape Area ({{lang-hu|Tájvédelmi körzet}}; abbr. TK) *National Nature Reserve ({{lang-hu|Természetvédelmi terület}}; abbr. TT)
