{{Japanese name|Shiga}}
[[File:Shigetaka Siga.jpg|thumb|Shiga Shigetaka]]
{{nihongo|'''Shiga Shigetaka'''|志賀 重昂||December 25, 1863&nbsp;– April 6, 1927}} was the editor of the [[magazine]] ''[[Nihonjin (magazine)|Nihonjin]]'' during the [[Meiji period]], in which he argued against extreme [[Westernization]].

